                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Fol. 1a: Praise of Wisdom (Wedasse Tebab). A praise of the Patriarchs from Enoch to Moses and Aaron. Special stress is laid on the holiness of the priestly clothes and the priestly liturgy --
                            Fol. 6a: The acts of Abraham (Gadla Abraham). An extract of this book has been published by Conti Rossini in his Appunti di storia e letteratua Falascia. Aescoly published the whole text in his Recueil de textes Falachas, according to the manuscript d'Abbadie 107 (Conti Rossini no.219). The present manuscript is better and serves to complete some of the lacunae of the d'Abbadie manuscript. --
                            Fol. 26a: The death of Isaac (Eraftu laIshaq) -- Fol. 44b: The death of Jacob (Filsatu laabuna Ya'qob) -- Fol. 60a: The homily of St. Ephraem Syrus on Abraham and Sarah</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1r">Fols 1r and following</locus>
                            <title>Wǝddāse ṭǝbab</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note>A praise of the Patriarchs from Enoch to Moses and Aaron. Special stress is laid on the holiness of the priestly clothes and the priestly liturgy</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="6r">Fols 6r and following</locus>
                            <title>Gadla Abraham</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <note>An extract of this book has been published by Conti Rossini <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/88PK6MTI"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1919Falascia"/><title level="a">Appunti di storia e letteratura Falascià</title><title level="j">Rivista degli Studi Orientali</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carlo</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Conti Rossini</t:surname></author><date>1919</date><biblScope unit="volume">8</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">563-610</biblScope><note type="url">https://www.jstor.org/stable/41923080</note></bibl>. Aescoly published the whole text in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/6BANA3I5"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Aescoly1951Recueil"/><title level="m">Recueil de textes falachas. Introduction. Textes éthiopiens. (édition critique et traduction). Index</title><title level="s">Travaux et mémoires de l’Institut d’ethnologie</title><author><forename>Aaron Zeev</forename><surname>Aešcoly</surname></author><pubPlace>Paris</pubPlace><publisher>Institut d’ethnologie</publisher><date>1951</date><series><title level="s">Travaux et mémoires de l’Institut d’ethnologie</title><biblScope unit="volume">55</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">55</biblScope><note type="url">https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k26168q.image</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Beta Esrael</note><note type="tag">bm:Aescoly1951Recueil</note></note><note type="tag">Beta Esrael</note><note type="tag">bm:Aescoly1951Recueil</note></bibl>, according to the manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb107">d'Abbadie 107 (Conti Rossini no.219)</ref>. The present manuscript is better and serves to complete some of the lacunae of the d'Abbadie manuscript.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="26r">Fols 26r and following</locus>
